CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776690659
OL,3,CPeople forced to suffer due to public
OL,4,Ctoilet 'deserts', health leaders warn
OL,6,F"Funding pressures have caused
OL,7,Fcouncils to rethink provision, the
OL,8,Fmaintenance of a public toilet could
OL,9,Fcost a council #25,000 a year, a
OL,10,Ffigure which is greatly impacted by
OL,11,Fthe condition in which they are left
OL,12,Fby their previous users.
OL,14,F"Vandalism and anti-social behaviour
OL,15,Fcost councils millions of pounds a
OL,16,Fyear which means councils having to
OL,17,Finvest into more regular cleaning and
OL,18,Fbetter security, meaning that the
OL,19,Ftaxpayer foots the bill for vandalism
OL,20,Fin this most basic of public
OL,21,Fprovisions.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31009
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776690659
OL,3,CPeople forced to suffer due to public
OL,4,Ctoilet 'deserts', health leaders warn
OL,6,F"Many councils have attempted to
OL,7,Faddress and prevent gaps in provision,
OL,8,Fby working with businesses to develop
OL,9,Fcommunity toilet schemes.
OL,11,F"However councils are acutely aware
OL,12,Fthat gaps in provision have opened
OL,13,Fdespite these efforts, for instance
OL,14,Fwhere businesses have closed on our
OL,15,Fhigh streets."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUwD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
